WINE QUALITY

Introduction Wine Quality DataSet

These datasets are related to data wine observation. This data frame contains the following columns: 1 - fixed acidity, 2 - volatile acidity, 3 - citric acid, 4 - residual sugar, 5 - chlorides, 6 - free sulfur dioxide, 7 - total sulfur dioxide, 8 - density, 9 - pH, 10 - sulphates, 11 - alcohol, 12 - quality.

/1 - pastovus rūgštingumas, 2 - lakusis rūgštingumas, 3 - citrinų rūgštis, 4 - likutinis cukrus, 5 - chloridai, 6 - laisvas sieros dioksidas, 7 - bendras sieros dioksidas, 8 - tankis, 9 - pH, 10 - sulfatai, 11 - alkoholis, 12 - kokybė./

The goals:

  1. On the dataset basis to describe the amount of various chemicals present in wine and their effect on its quality.
  2. To review Study case based on Wine's review with the purpose to prove the world statistics of the list of the best wines.

Analysis Results

We have 5 types of quality in DataSet - 3 to 8

The Best quality 8. The less quality 3. The elements of highest effect on the quality of wine:

1 - Alcohol; 2 - Free sulfur dioxide; 3 - Total sulfur dioxide;

The elements that not much important to effect on the quality of wine:

1 - Fixed acidity 2 - Volatile acidity 3 - Citric acid 4 - Residual sugar 5 - Chlorides 6 - Density 7 - PH 8 - Sulphates

If you drink wine, please pay attention to these items.

In [23]:
def resumetable(df):
    print(f"Dataset Shape: {df.shape}")
    summary = pd.DataFrame(df.dtypes,columns=['dtypes'])
    summary = summary.reset_index()
    summary['Name'] = summary['index']
    summary = summary[['Name','dtypes']]
    summary['Missing'] = df.isnull().sum().values    
    summary['Uniques'] = df.nunique().values
    summary['First Value'] = df.loc[0].values
    summary['Second Value'] = df.loc[1].values
    summary['Third Value'] = df.loc[2].values

    for name in summary['Name'].value_counts().index:
        summary.loc[summary['Name'] == name, 'Entropy'] = round(stats.entropy(df[name].value_counts(normalize=True), base=2),2) 

    return summary

Designation

The vineyard within the winery where the grapes that made the wine are from. A vineyard is a plantation of grape-bearing wines, grown mainly for winemaking, but also raisins, table grapes and non-alcoholic grape juice. The science, practice and study of wineyard production is known as viticulture Winery A Winery is a building or property that produces wine, or a business involved in the production of wine, such as a wine company.

Province The province or state that the wine is from

Region1 The wine growing area in a province or state
